      • getIndex

        public int getIndex()
        Gets the index of this Result in the tree of Results, this is not like a normal array index in which it goes 0-n but instead can skip many different numbers if those Results have never existed. For example you may have one Result with an index of 1 and then the next is at 4.
        Returns:
        the index of this Result in relation to the tree
